WHAT IS FUNCTION ?
     A function is block of code designed to perform a particular task.
     A JS function is executed when something invokes it(calls it).
WHY FUNCTIONS ?
     You can reuse code:Define code once ,and use it many times
     You can use same code many times with different arguments,to produce different results.
WHAT IS FUNCTION ARGUMENTS ?
    Arguments are passed by value.
    The parameters in a function call,are the function arguments.
    Js arguments are passed by value.
    The function only gets to known the values,not the arguments locations.
WHAT IS FUNCTION CALL() ?
   The call() method is a predefined javascript method.
   It can be used to invoke a method with an owner object as an argument(parameter)
   With call(),an object can use a method belonging to another object.
WHAT IS CLOSURE FUNCTION ?
    A closure is the combination of a function bundled together(enclosed)with references to its surrounding state .
    In JS,closures are the primary mechanism used to enable data privacy.